The leadership of the National Association of Nigerian Students has applauded the Governor of Ogun State, Prince Dapo Abiodun for acquiring over 120 patrol vehicles and motorbikes for police to combat crime. NANS Public Relations Officer, Comrade Azeez Adeyemi in a statement on Friday in Abuja, said the effort to support the police was commendable, especially in the face of current security challenges confronting the nation. ALSO READ: OSUSTECH lecturer kidnapped in Kogi Rivers: APC set to put its house in order Xenophobic attacks: Malami makes case for overhauling of… Residents groan as flood disrupts commercial in Warri,… Osun govt tackles Makinde over comments on LAUTECH He said the student body was appreciative of the Governor’s decision to strengthen the police for the protection of lives and property in the state. “Ogun state housed a large number of our students as the state has the largest number of institutions across the country. “We want to also appeal to the recipients, the police to make judicious use of them to end criminal activities in the interest of the state,” he said. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
